liangmicha:
I solved the issue by setting `exifdata` to `null` on the img tag before the `EXIF.getData`
```
      var imgTag = $('.thumbnail > img')[0];
      imgTag.exifdata = null;

      EXIF.getData(imgTag, function() {
        var allMetaData = EXIF.getAllTags(this);
        console.log(allMetaData);
      });
```

No need to remove and re-add the `img` tag, or cache busting.. I solved the issue by setting `exifdata` to `null` on the img tag before the `EXIF.getData`
```
      var imgTag = $('.thumbnail > img')[0];
      imgTag.exifdata = null;

      EXIF.getData(imgTag, function() {
        var allMetaData = EXIF.getAllTags(this);
        console.log(allMetaData);
      });
```

